HEADWORD: Encyclopedism
<hw>En*cy`clo*pe"dism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The art of
writing or compiling encyclopedias; also, possession of the whole range
of knowledge; encyclopedic learning.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Encyclopedist</ent>⟦br⟧
